DESCRIPTION:The humans have vanished\, and you’ve just landed on Earth. Join one of three expeditions and unravel the clues they left behind. Hidden in plain sight are clues about the paintings in Beneath the Turning Sky for you to solve and find your way out of the exhibition space!\nJoin us for this mystery-filled adventure!\nThis programme is hosted in conjunction with the Teen Takeover programme.
DTEND:20260606T053000Z
DTSTART:20260606T043000Z
SUMMARY:Escaping our Existence
UID:1289@map-india.org
URL:https://map-india.org/map-events/escaping-our-existence/
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://map-india.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/WhatsApp-Image-2026-02-25-at-18.00.29.jpeg
CATEGORIES:Performances,MAP,CBD
DTSTAMP:20260522T114213Z
DESCRIPTION:Long before the language of inclusion entered our workplaces\, India held space for gender in all its complexity through diverse cultural and spiritual traditions. The Jogappas are one such living tradition — a transgender community whose identity\, livelihood\, and spiritual practice have remained deeply intertwined for centuries through devotion to Goddess Yellamma.\n\nSacred Rhythms\, Living Histories of Jogappa community invites audiences into this world through an intimate cultural experience where music\, storytelling\, and handmade instruments carry forward a tradition rooted at the intersection of faith\, folklore\, and identity. Drawing from rich oral histories across north Karnataka\, south Maharashtra\, west Telangana\, and Andhra Pradesh\, the Jogappas perform devotional compositions in praise of Goddess Yellamma while sharing glimpses into their lived realities and cultural heritage.\n\nIn collaboration with the Solidarity Foundation\, this interactive session brings together the lived cultural knowledge of the Jogappa tradition and academic perspectives on its history\, music\, and spiritual practice\, offering audiences a rare opportunity to listen closely\, engage meaningfully\, and deepen their understanding of this powerful living art form.
DTEND:20260606T140000Z
DTSTART:20260606T123000Z
SUMMARY:Sacred Rhythms\, Living Histories of Jogappa community
UID:1293@map-india.org
URL:https://map-india.org/map-events/sacred-rhythms-living-histories-of-jogappa-community/
END:VEVENT
