BEGIN:VEVENT
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://map-india.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/Untitled-design-3.png
CATEGORIES:Guided Walk,MAP,CBD
DTSTAMP:20260520T050508Z
DESCRIPTION:Join us for a guided walk of the exhibition Paper Gardens: Art\, Botany\, and Empire by Breanne Coelho from the MAP Team.\nBetween the 17th and 20th centuries\, the Indian subcontinent was the site of extensive botanical surveys under colonial rule. Plant collection and classification were closely tied to imperial economic\, medical\, and political interests\, and botanical illustration played a central role in this project. \nBringing together a new and historically significant collection of botanical art from this period\, the exhibition draws on recent scholarship to recover the often uncredited identities and histories of the Indian artists who made them.
DTEND:20260531T111500Z
DTSTART:20260531T103000Z
SUMMARY:Paper Gardens: Art\, Botany and Empire
UID:1279@map-india.org
URL:https://map-india.org/map-events/paper-gardens-art-botany-and-empire/
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://map-india.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/Screenshot-2026-05-22-165600.png
CATEGORIES:Film Screenings,MAP,CBD
DTSTAMP:20260522T122534Z
DESCRIPTION:Join us for a weekend of queer short film screenings that bring into focus stories of identity\, resistance\, joy\, and community from across the country. Through intimate and thought-provoking narratives\, these films explore the realities of queer lives\, reflecting on visibility\, belonging\, resilience\, and self-expression in a time marked by increasing invisibilisation and protest.\n\nSpanning diverse experiences and perspectives\, the screenings invite audiences to engage with stories that challenge silence and reclaim space through the power of storytelling. Accompanied by conversations and reflections with speakers and community voices\, the programme creates space for dialogue rooted in solidarity\, and queer joy.\n\nThe film list will be announced shortly.\n\nThis programme is part of LGBTQIA+ programming and is an attempt to amplify narratives from within the queer community through film\, dialogue\, and collective reflection.
DTEND:20260607T113000Z
DTSTART:20260606T093000Z
SUMMARY:Queer Film Evenings
UID:1295@map-india.org
URL:https://map-india.org/map-events/queer-film-evenings/
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://map-india.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/Screenshot-2026-05-22-160624.png
CATEGORIES: Featuring,MAP,CBD
